> Who among us has made a better comeback than the mighty cauliflower? Once considered uninteresting (at best), this versatile vegetable can now be spotted as a pizza crust, rice substitute, and even a hearty taco filling! Here you'll roast cumin-seasoned florets until crisp and golden. Paired with a tangy-sweet cabbage slaw, a lightly spicy curry-infused mayo, and a garnish of fresh chopped cilantro, these vegan mashup tacos are satisfying as all get-out and so loaded with bold flavors, no one will miss the meat.

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @cauliflower florets{10%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon}, @cumin{1%teaspoon}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{18-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, zest and halve @lime{1}. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

Open package of @chopped chicken breast{10%ounce} and drain off any excess liquid. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken in a single layer; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

== Cabbage Slaw ==

In a #large bowl{}, combine @sugar{1/2%teaspoon}, @salt{1/2%tsp}, and juice from the lime (1 tsp sugar and 1 tsp salt for 4 servings). Stir until sugar dissolves. Add @coleslaw mix{4%ounce} and as much lime zest as you like; toss until thoroughly combined. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

== Curry Mayo ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @vegan mayonnaise{4%tablespoon}, @curry powder{1%teaspoon}, and @sugar{1/4%teaspoon} (2 tsp curry powder and 1/2 tsp sugar for 4). Stir until thoroughly combined. Add @water{1%tsp} at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

== Assembly ==

Once cauliflower is done roasting, place @flour tortillas{6} on a second baking sheet and bake on top rack until lightly browned, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Divide tortillas between plates; spread with a thin layer of curry mayo. Top with roasted cauliflower and slaw. Garnish tacos with cilantro and drizzle with any remaining curry mayo. Serve.

Top tortillas with chicken along with roasted cauliflower and slaw.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.